the stability of my income. I prepare myself for the worst case scenarios that may happen, but I still get taken by surprise. I keep trying new things to generate more stable income, to improve my performances and to emancipate myself and be self-sufficient, to not have to depend on the guy for 4person shit salary exchange and bullshit sports supplements. Since I express myself only through fitness and athletism I have too much time, to rest, to think, ponder in the gym. I’m pretty much left alone by people who used to follow me, like IMMUOTION only active on facebook and my forum, but I don’t care. I continue doing my thing, trying to do my thing well. My cutting season is not famous music-wise, but people do like what I do.

I feel more and more empty, isolated. I start to feel hypocritical. I felt unprepared and ignorant in college, but I knew that was what I had to do. I was a fool, but I followed my heart and taught myself, filled my mind with all that knowledge that though universities and authorities keep, cause I wanted to explore myself, everything that I have on this magical planet. Everything that makes me tick, everything that allows me to create and find feel and get somehow inner peace…

It’s not easy for me anymore these 8/9 years because I’m older and have more experience yet I seem to be lost at sea I try to figure out my place
